{"lemma":"سَرابُ","slug":"سَرابُ","root":"س.ر.ب","root_slug":"س-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَراب","root":"سرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19464"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mirage, fata morgana","examples":[{"text":"وَٱلَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا أَعْمَالُهُمْ كَسَرَابٍ بِقِيعَةٍ يَحْسَبُهُ ٱلظَّمْآنُ مَاءً حَتَّىٰ إِذَا جَاءَهُ لَمْ يَجِدْهُ شَيْئًا وَوَجَدَ ٱللَّهَ عِنْدَهُ فَوَفَّاهُ حِسَابَهُ. وَٱللَّهُ سَرِيعُ ٱلْحِسَابِ.","english":"As for the faithless, their works are like a mirage in a plain, which the thirsty man supposes to be water. When he comes to it, he finds it to be nothing; but there he finds God, who will pay him his full account, and God is swift at reckoning."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"phantom"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sewage"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From سَرِبَ (sariba, “to flow”)."},"ipa":["/sa.raːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19464","headword_ar":"سَرَابٌ","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mirage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lN","text_ar":"ا=لٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, M, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of running water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at midday,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaving to the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in appearance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowering everything so that it becomes"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaving to the ground, having no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoS","text_ar":"شَخْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) whereas the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=l","text_ar":"ا=ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuHaY","text_ar":"ضُحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or early part of the day when the sun is yet low], raising figures seen from a distance, and making them to quiver: (M:) [several other distinctions between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srAb","text_ar":"سراب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=l","text_ar":"ا=ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned here in the TA, see voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lN","text_ar":"ا=لٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbN","text_ar":"سَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has no pl. (S and K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaArN","text_ar":"نَهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodaEu","text_ar":"اَخْدَعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino saraAbK","text_ar":"مِنْ سَرَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More deceitful than a middaymirage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbi","text_ar":"سَرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAmi","text_ar":"قَطَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K, TA,) i. e. indecl., with kesr for its termination, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbu","text_ar":"سَرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", imperfectly decl., (TA,) determinate, (K, TA,) as a proper name, not having the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it, (TA,) is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel of El-Basoos"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albasuws","text_ar":"البَسُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the she-camel El-Basoos,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA,) for El-Basoos was her surname: (TA:) whence the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oA^amu mino","text_ar":"اَشْاَمُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbi","text_ar":"سَرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More inauspicious than Sarábi"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, K, TA:) a celebrated prov.: for she was the cause of a famous war. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["As","M","TA","S","A","K"]}]}}